anni Staunovo🛢", "followers": 120883, "views": 51592, "likes": 30, "replies": 0, "retweets": 4, "quotes": 1, "bookmarks": 4, "labels": {"relevant": true, "price_sentiment": "Bullish", "emotional_sentiment": "Neutral", "topics": ["Tankers/shipping", "Iran"]}}, {"id": "2066797775950344377", "url": "https://x.com/JavierBlas/status/2066797775950344377", "text": "CHART OF THE DAY: What goes into backwardation, can go into contango. \n\nThe time spreads of some key Middle Eastern crude grades have collapsed. Murban from UAE is now in contago, even before Hormuz formally re-opens with the signing of the deal, scheduled for Friday. https://t.co/vq8Px3DuhU", "time": "08:19", "author": "JavierBlas", "author_name": "Javier Blas", "followers": 393796, "views": 58246, "likes": 411, "replies": 18, "retweets": 94, "quotes": 9, "bookmarks": 61, "labels": {"relevant": true, "price_sentiment": "Bearish", "emotional_sentiment": "Neutral", "topics": ["Prices/technicals", "Iran"]}}, {"id": "2066803751931797530", "url": "https://x.com/JavierBlas/status/2066803751931797530", "text": "COLUMN: The Chinese 'oil weapon.'\n\nThe Strait of Hormuz crisis shows Beijing is now a stabilizing force for oil prices. This potentially reshapes the energy risk premia — and Asian geopolitics if conflict breaks out over Taiwan. \n\n@Opinion https://t.co/LLuf9cdzrw", "time": "08:43", "author": "JavierBlas", "author_name": "Javier Blas", "followers": 393796, "views": 625420, "likes": 1075, "replies": 37, "retweets": 238, "quotes": 34, "bookmarks": 383, "labels": {"relevant": true, "price_sentiment": "Bearish", "emotional_sentiment": "Neutral", "topics": ["China demand", "Geopolitics"]}}, {"id": "2066815080076046585", "url": "https://x.com/Amena__Bakr/status/2066815080076046585", "text": "Most replacement vessels are still far from the Gulf, so shipping capacity cannot be restored instantly. #OOTT", "time": "09:28", "author": "Amena__Bakr", "author_name": "Amena Bakr", "followers": 174705, "views": 15052, "likes": 70, "replies": 16, "retweets": 15, "quotes": 1, "bookmarks": 2, "labels": {"relevant": true, "price_sentiment": "Bullish", "emotional_sentiment": "Neutral", "topics": ["Tankers/shipping", "Supply outlook"]}}, {"id": "2066830843310489630", "url": "https://x.com/JavierBlas/status/2066830843310489630", "text": "\"... every day WTI is above $75...", "time": "10:30", "author": "JavierBlas", "author_name": "Javier Blas", "followers": 393796, "views": 127118, "likes": 277, "replies": 46, "retweets": 24, "quotes": 8, "bookmarks": 22, "labels": {"relevant": true, "price_sentiment": "Bearish", "emotional_sentiment": "Negative", "topics": ["Prices/technicals"]}}, {"id": "2066835921098432648", "url": "https://x.com/JavierBlas/status/2066835921098432648", "text": "My colleagues at Bloomberg News are reporting Qatar plans to restore ~50% of its LNG production in just four weeks after SoH re-opens, and ~80% in two months.\n\nAnd that's LNG, which requires a lot of work to re-start. Imagine what everyone else is going to do with oil output.", "time": "10:50", "author": "JavierBlas", "author_name": "Javier Blas", "followers": 393796, "views": 286209, "likes": 1686, "replies": 84, "retweets": 317, "quotes": 50, "bookmarks": 160, "labels": {"relevant": true, "price_sentiment": "Bearish", "emotional_sentiment": "Neutral", "topics": ["Natural gas", "Supply outlook"]}}, {"id": "2066836368878080226", "url": "https://x.com/JavierBlas/status/2066836368878080226", "text": "Chinese coal-fired electricity generation rose again in May (up 2.4% y-on-y), hitting the highest ever level for that month. \n\nSo far this year, China has set seasonal record highs of coal-fired generation in every month of 2026 despite strong solar / wind investments.", "time": "10:52", "author": "JavierBlas", "author_name": "Javier Blas", "followers": 393796, "views": 42742, "likes": 269, "replies": 20, "retweets": 83, "quotes": 23, "bookmarks": 23, "labels": {"relevant": true, "price_sentiment": "Neutral", "emotional_sentiment": "Neutral", "topics": ["China demand"]}}, {"id": "2066853007699091725", "url": "https://x.com/Amena__Bakr/status/2066853007699091725", "text": "As of 15 June, confirmed crossings through the monitored Strait of Hormuz zone remained flat d/d at five, covering both commercial and non-commercial traffic. @Kpler -#OOTT", "time": "11:58", "author": "Amena__Bakr", "author_name": "Amena Bakr", "followers": 174705, "views": 17176, "likes": 128, "replies": 7, "retweets": 28, "quotes": 2, "bookmarks": 9, "labels": {"relevant": true, "price_sentiment": "Bullish", "emotional_sentiment": "Neutral", "topics": ["Tankers/shipping", "Iran"]}}, {"id": "2066858755917017284", "url": "https://x.com/JavierBlas/status/2066858755917017284", "text": "Dubai crude oil physical premia has gone NEGATIVE for the first time since early 2026. Back in mid-March, it reached an stratospheric level of plus $65 a barrel. Today, it's minus 33 cents a barrel.", "time": "12:21", "author": "JavierBlas", "author_name": "Javier Blas", "followers": 393796, "views": 153503, "likes": 750, "replies": 30, "retweets": 139, "quotes": 10, "bookmarks": 73, "labels": {"relevant": true, "price_sentiment": "Bearish", "emotional_sentiment": "Neutral", "topics": ["Prices/technicals"]}}, {"id": "2066897503094505612", "url": "https://x.com/JavierBlas/status/2066897503094505612", "text": "The Iranian oil tanker fleet has started to move, with at least one VLCC (DIONA, 9569695) crossing the US Navy blockade line (to be seen what the US does). Another tanker is approaching the line, while others are moving on their way into the Iranian oil terminals to load. https://t.co/XWBntP7xwM", "time": "14:55", "author": "JavierBlas", "author_name": "Javier Blas", "followers": 393796, "views": 52469, "likes": 384, "replies": 19, "retweets": 88, "quotes": 8, "bookmarks": 25, "labels": {"relevant": true, "price_sentiment": "Bearish", "emotional_sentiment": "Neutral", "topics": ["Iran", "Tankers/shipping"]}}, {"id": "2066937009495503298", "url": "https://x.com/JavierBlas/status/2066937009495503298", "text": "As I warned before⤵️, \"the oil is the money.\" \n\nIgnore the Qatari frozen funds, the UAE bank accounts, and focus on the oil waivers. That's how Tehran would make the money, even more so if it can repatriate the funds. From WSJ: https://t.co/fYPQglJ21J", "time": "17:32", "author": "JavierBlas", "author_name": "Javier Blas", "followers": 393796, "views": 62826, "likes": 267, "replies": 16, "retweets": 50, "quotes": 5, "bookmarks": 51, "labels": {"relevant": true, "price_sentiment": "Bearish", "emotional_sentiment": "Neutral", "topics": ["Iran", "Geopolitics"]}}, {"id": "2066983617402654906", "url": "https://x.com/JuliOnTwtr/status/2066983617402654906", "text": "API Inventory Moves 06/16\n\nCrude -8.33 million (exp. -4.5 million)\nGasoline +2.479\nDistillates\nCushing \n\nSPR actual -8.9 million (lowest levels since.... 1983)\n#oott #crudeoil #gasoline #API", "time": "20:37", "author": "JuliOnTwtr", "author_name": "Julianne Geiger", "followers": 8674, "views": 89595, "likes": 198, "replies": 19, "retweets": 25, "quotes": 9, "bookmarks": 11, "labels": {"relevant": true, "price_sentiment": "Bullish", "emotional_sentiment": "Neutral", "topics": ["US inventories"]}}, {"id": "2066984895063249152", "url": "https://x.com/JuliOnTwtr/status/2066984895063249152", "text": "API Inventory Moves 06/16\n\nCrude -8.33 million (exp. -4.5 million)\nGasoline +2.479 million \nDistillates -461,000\nCushing -1.523 million \n\nSPR actual -8.9 million (lowest levels since.... 1983)\n#oott #crudeoil #gasoline #API", "time": "20:42", "author": "JuliOnTwtr", "author_name": "Julianne Geiger", "followers": 8674, "views": 88379, "likes": 214, "replies": 26, "retweets": 48, "quotes": 16, "bookmarks": 18, "labels": {"relevant": true, "price_sentiment": "Bullish", "emotional_sentiment": "Neutral", "topics": ["US inventories"]}}], "top_authors_by_tweets": [{"username": "staunovo", "name": "Giovanni Staunovo🛢", "f